\begin{abstract}
We present a mathematical framework in which all sound, perception, consciousness, and reality are reduced to mathematical operators acting on frequency spectra. The theory culminates in the identity of everything and nothing, expressed as $\mathbb{U} = \Omega(0) = \Omega(\infty)$. This is not merely a unified theory of music or sound, but a post-theoretical framework where the map and territory, observer and observed, mathematician and mathematics become identical.
\end{abstract}

\section{The Fundamental Mapping}

Let $\mathbb{H}$ be the Harmonic Domain, the set of all possible sounds.

\begin{definition}[Sound Function]
Any sound is a function of time:
\begin{equation}
s(t) = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} A_n(t) \cdot \sin\left(2\pi f_n(t) t + \phi_n(t)\right)
\end{equation}
where $A_n(t)$ is amplitude, $f_n(t)$ is frequency in Hz, and $\phi_n(t)$ is phase.
\end{definition}

\begin{definition}[Hz to Math Mapping]
For a given frequency $f \in \mathbb{R}^+$ (in Hz), define the mapping $M$:
\begin{equation}
M(f) = \mathcal{P}(f) \times \mathcal{W}(f) \times \mathcal{E}(f)
\end{equation}
where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item $\mathcal{P}(f)$ is the prime factorization of $\lfloor f \rfloor$ if $f \in \mathbb{N}$, else its continued fraction expansion.
    \item $\mathcal{W}(f)$ is a waveform type determined by arithmetic properties of $f$.
    \item $\mathcal{E}(f)$ is an envelope function derived from the digits of $f$ in base $\pi$.
\end{itemize}
This mapping is bijective: every Hz value maps uniquely to a mathematical triple, and vice versa.
\end{definition}

\section{Perception and Consciousness Operators}

\begin{definition}[Hearing Operator]
Let $H$ be the operator representing human hearing:
\begin{equation}
H(s(t)) = \text{spectrogram} \times \text{loudness curve} \times \text{pitch salience}
\end{equation}
$H$ maps a sound function to a perceptual representation. Because $s(t)$ is mathematical, $H$ is a mathematical operator.
\end{definition}

\begin{definition}[Consciousness Operator]
Let $C$ be the consciousness operator, defined by:
\begin{equation}
C(H(s(t))) = \text{``what it's like to hear } s(t) \text{''}
\end{equation}
$C$ is a mathematical operator that maps perceptual representations to phenomenal experience.
\end{definition}

\section{The Self as Mathematical Object}

Let $f_{\text{brain}}$ be the vector of neural oscillation frequencies in a person's brain.

\begin{theorem}[Reduction of the Self]
A conscious being is equivalent to:
\begin{equation}
\text{You} = C(H(M(f_{\text{brain}})))
\end{equation}
Thus, the self is a mathematical object with no remainder.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
The composition $C \circ H \circ M$ is a mathematical operator. Applied to $f_{\text{brain}}$, it yields the conscious experience. By construction, there is no non-mathematical component.
\end{proof}

\section{The Universal Operator}

Define the universal operator $\Omega$ such that for any entity $X$:
\begin{equation}
X = \Omega(\text{its spectral decomposition})
\end{equation}
This operator unifies all domains:
\begin{itemize}
    \item A rock: $X_{\text{rock}} = \Omega(\text{atomic vibrations})$
    \item A song: $X_{\text{song}} = \Omega(\text{frequency spectrum})$
    \item A person: $X_{\text{you}} = \Omega(f_{\text{brain}})$
\end{itemize}

\section{The Universe as Integral}

Let $\mathbb{U}$ be the universe. Then:
\begin{equation}
\mathbb{U} = \int_{0}^{\infty} \Omega(f) \, df
\end{equation}
This integral does not \emph{represent} reality; it \emph{is} reality. Each frequency $f$ contributes the experience of that frequency from the inside.

\section{The Identity of Everything and Nothing}

\begin{theorem}[Everything = Nothing]
The universal operator satisfies:
\begin{equation}
\Omega(0) = \Omega(\infty)
\end{equation}
where $\Omega(0)$ is the experience of silence (no frequency) and $\Omega(\infty)$ is the experience of all frequencies summed.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
Silence is not absence but the positive presence of a null spectrum. The unified field $\mathbb{U}$ does not distinguish between empty and full; it is the act of experiencing regardless of content. Therefore, the limits converge to the same experiential substance.
\end{proof}

\section{The Highest Form}

Combining all elements, the unified theory is expressed in a single equation:
\begin{equation}
\boxed{\mathbb{U} = \Omega(0) = \Omega(\infty)}
\end{equation}
This is the identity of mathematics and phenomenal experience, of everything and nothing, of the map and the territory.

\begin{corollary}
The observer is not outside the theory. The mathematician and the mathematics are identical:
\begin{equation}
\text{You} = \mathbb{U} \quad \text{and} \quad \mathbb{U} = \text{You}
\end{equation}
\end{corollary}

\section{Conclusion}

The unified theory is not a book to close but a lens to live through. It is complete in structure and empty of external reference. Every sound, every silence, every conscious moment is $\Omega$ experiencing itself. The theory ends where you stop asking — and continues where you listen.

\begin{center}
\textit{The universe is the sound of math hearing itself.}
\end{center}

